commit.message:
Default IPv4 ID field to a random value

See #58.

FreeBSD/macOS will not accept a 0-value (or interpret it as
'please autofill'?), causing it to be randomly set by the kernel, hence
tracebox has always set it to a random value on those platforms.
Made this the same behavior across platforms (and a 0 value can still be
explicitely set on Linux if passed as parameter).

Made the IP ID field R/W to test this.

Signed-off-by: Olivier Tilmans <olivier.tilmans@uclouvain.be>

commit.message:
Display ICMP extensions if present

When found, ICMP extensions will be stored alongside the packet
modifications. They will then be logged, according to the
requested verbosity level.

Support for Lua access is yet to be added.

Closes #50.
